********** README for using CMU's node-movement **************
            ************** file generators ************

A.scenario or node-movement file generator
---------------------------
Directory:
~ns/indep-utils/cmu-scen-gen/setdest

Files:
Makefile
setdest.h setdest.cc
make-scen.csh


Steps for creating scenario files for mobility simulations :

1.Create an archive of ns library files by adding the following lines to
your Makefile under ns directory:

libns.a: $(OBJ)
        $(RM) $@
        $(AR) $@ $(OBJ)
        $(RANLIB) $@
"make libns.a" to create an archive for ns.  

2. Make the following changes in your Makefile in setdest directory to
include paths to the ns directory and nslib. Add/edit the following:

INCLUDES = -I. -I/usr/openwin/include \
        -I/Full/Path/To/ns-2/Directory \
        -I/Full/Path/To/tclcl \
        -I/Full/Path/To/otcl \
        -I/Full/Path/To/tk8.0/tk8.0/include \
        -I/Full/Path/To/tcl8.0/tcl8.0/include 

Next add path to the libraries:
LIBS = -L/Full/Path/To/ns-2 -lns \
        -L/Full/Path/To/tclcl -ltclcl \
        -L/Full/Path/To/otcl -lotcl \
        -L/Full/Path/To/tk8.0/tk8.0/lib -ltk80 \
        -L/Full/Path/To/tcl8.0/tcl8.0/lib -ltcl80 \
        -lXext -lX11 \
        -lnsl -ldl \
        -lm -ldl     

setdest: setdest.o
        $(CCX) -o setdest $@.o $(LDFLAGS) $(CFLAGS) $(INCLUDES) $(LIBS)

and,

.cc.o:
        $(CCX) -c $(CFLAGS) $(INCLUDES) -o $@ $*.cc

3. Save your Makefile and run "make" to create executable setdest.

4. Run setdest with arguments in the following way:
./setdest -n <num_of_nodes> -p <pausetime> -s <maxspeed> -t <simtime> \
      -x <maxx> -y <maxy> > <outdir>/<scenario-file>

Example: ./setdest -n 20 -p 2.0 -s 10.0 -t 200 -x 500 -y 500 >
scen-20-test
and the output will be written in a file called scen-20-test.

4a. OR run make-scen.csh to generate multiple scenario files.

Note: The nodes created are indexed starting from 1. Edit setdest.cc
incase you want the indexing to start from 0.
